General.Name: Gladiator Metals Corp
General.Description: Gladiator Metals Corp. engages in the acquisition, development, and operation of mineral property. The company explores for copper, molybdenum, silver, gold, zinc, nickel, and lead minerals. It holds an option to acquire 100% interest in the Whitehorse copper project comprising 315 contiguous claims covering an area of approximately 5,380 hectares located in the Whitehorse mining district, Yukon territory, Canada. The company is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
General.Address: 1430 - 800 West Pender Street, Vancouver, BC, Canada, V6C 2V6
